  "texts": [
    "A204, page 9 of 15 Overall, none of the current models in the literature are able to explain the non-evolving mass ratio q ∼ 0.7 in conjunction with rapid evolution of the primary mass with redshift that we find with (H)DPGMM.",
    "This might indicate that astrophysical models fail to describe some key physical process, such as the efficiency of mass accretion and angular momentum transport during mass transfer (e.g.",
    "Gallegos-Garcia et al. 2023; Willcox et al. 2023), the impact of stellar rotation (e.g.",
    "Mapelli et al. 2020; Marchant & Moriya 2020; Riley et al. 2021), or the efficiency of dynamical assembly (e.g.",
    "Fragione & 2018; Mapelli et al. 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Gallegos-Garcia et al. 2023; Willcox et al. 2023), the impact of stellar rotation (e.g.",
